00:12:43.421 --> 00:12:43.730 align:middle line:90%


00:12:43.730 --> 00:12:44.530 align:middle line:90%
Hi.

00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:45.330 align:middle line:90%
Welcome back.

00:12:45.330 --> 00:12:47.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm Carolyn Craft, speaking
with Catherine Lenard.

00:12:47.730 --> 00:12:50.350 align:middle line:84%
She is author of the
book "All I Ever Wanted

00:12:50.350 --> 00:12:52.310 align:middle line:84%
Was a Lot of Money
and A Husband,

00:12:52.310 --> 00:12:55.960 align:middle line:84%
and Instead I Did
Get Enlightenment."

00:12:55.960 --> 00:12:58.407 align:middle line:10%
I think we all go after that
at some point in our life,

00:12:58.407 --> 00:13:00.490 align:middle line:10%
that there's something
outside of ourselves that's

00:13:00.490 --> 00:13:03.207 align:middle line:10%
going to help us have
the happiness and success

00:13:03.207 --> 00:13:04.040 align:middle line:10%
that we really want.

00:13:04.040 --> 00:13:06.790 align:middle line:84%
And we're really
understanding and learning

00:13:06.790 --> 00:13:09.520 align:middle line:90%
that it is an inside job.

00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:14.200 align:middle line:10%
You had an experience with
a relationship, David,

00:13:14.200 --> 00:13:17.260 align:middle line:10%
where he introduced you
to the celestial tones.

00:13:17.260 --> 00:13:19.210 align:middle line:84%
And you said it was a
beautiful experience.

00:13:19.210 --> 00:13:22.570 align:middle line:84%
Give us an idea of what
that was like for you.

00:13:22.570 --> 00:13:25.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, Carolyn, it was
absolutely awesome.

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:26.740 align:middle line:10%
You know, again, it was being--

00:13:26.740 --> 00:13:29.280 align:middle line:10%
we were under extreme
circumstances.

00:13:29.280 --> 00:13:31.780 align:middle line:10%
There were some physical things
that were going on with him.

00:13:31.780 --> 00:13:36.250 align:middle line:84%
And I just felt incredible
unconditional love

00:13:36.250 --> 00:13:37.810 align:middle line:90%
for this person.

00:13:37.810 --> 00:13:42.070 align:middle line:84%
And he, having the ability
to see into other dimensions

00:13:42.070 --> 00:13:46.450 align:middle line:84%
was able to call my attention
to interdimensional beings that

00:13:46.450 --> 00:13:48.550 align:middle line:90%
began to fill the room.

00:13:48.550 --> 00:13:51.760 align:middle line:84%
And at a certain
point, I saw light

00:13:51.760 --> 00:13:54.940 align:middle line:84%
streams that were
coming down toward him.

00:13:54.940 --> 00:13:57.130 align:middle line:84%
And I saw an actual
grid formation

00:13:57.130 --> 00:13:58.690 align:middle line:90%
that was around my body.

00:13:58.690 --> 00:14:01.170 align:middle line:90%
Some might know it as a merkaba.

00:14:01.170 --> 00:14:02.670 align:middle line:84%
I don't know exactly
how to term it.

00:14:02.670 --> 00:14:05.110 align:middle line:84%
I would just prefer to
say that it was beautiful,

00:14:05.110 --> 00:14:07.000 align:middle line:84%
with tetrahedrons
spinning in it.

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:11.530 align:middle line:84%
And the feeling was just of
amazingly incredible love.

00:14:11.530 --> 00:14:14.260 align:middle line:84%
And actually heard
celestial tones,

00:14:14.260 --> 00:14:17.470 align:middle line:84%
which was, I don't know how
to explain that exactly, it's

00:14:17.470 --> 00:14:18.800 align:middle line:90%
just I've come to recognize it.

00:14:18.800 --> 00:14:20.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Music not of this world.

00:14:20.270 --> 00:14:22.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you very much.

00:14:22.690 --> 00:14:25.660 align:middle line:84%
Oh, subtle vision,
subtle hearing,

00:14:25.660 --> 00:14:29.120 align:middle line:84%
something not seen or heard
with the regular five senses.

00:14:29.120 --> 00:14:32.110 align:middle line:84%
And it was such a privilege
and such an honor.

00:14:32.110 --> 00:14:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And it gave me the
knowledge, bar none,

00:14:34.900 --> 00:14:38.170 align:middle line:84%
that there's so much more than
this third dimensional reality

00:14:38.170 --> 00:14:40.270 align:middle line:84%
that we're all
walking around in.

00:14:40.270 --> 00:14:45.130 align:middle line:84%
>> What, for you, what
was the purpose, the gift,

00:14:45.130 --> 00:14:47.200 align:middle line:90%
in that experience?

00:14:47.200 --> 00:14:49.780 align:middle line:90%
How did that change your life?

00:14:49.780 --> 00:14:54.190 align:middle line:84%
>> I think I began to understand
that the more that I could open

00:14:54.190 --> 00:14:59.410 align:middle line:84%
my heart by being vulnerable
and honest in my day-to-day

00:14:59.410 --> 00:15:03.990 align:middle line:84%
dealings with people, that
would allow the heart to open,

00:15:03.990 --> 00:15:06.020 align:middle line:90%
let the defenses come down.

00:15:06.020 --> 00:15:09.400 align:middle line:84%
And through that open heart,
all kinds of magical things

00:15:09.400 --> 00:15:11.740 align:middle line:84%
open to us that
aren't really there

00:15:11.740 --> 00:15:14.860 align:middle line:84%
for walking around,
like defensive and upset

00:15:14.860 --> 00:15:17.140 align:middle line:84%
and just keeping
people at a distance.

00:15:17.140 --> 00:15:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So the more that I found
that I open my heart,

00:15:19.990 --> 00:15:21.940 align:middle line:90%
the more that became accessible.

00:15:21.940 --> 00:15:26.320 align:middle line:84%
>> When you open your heart and
you feel that vulnerability,

00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:30.735 align:middle line:84%
how do you balance the
things that come up from that

00:15:30.735 --> 00:15:32.860 align:middle line:84%
openhearted space, where
you're out there where you

00:15:32.860 --> 00:15:33.700 align:middle line:90%
haven't been before?

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:36.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you're in a
relationship with someone,

00:15:36.220 --> 00:15:38.140 align:middle line:84%
a business
relationship, and you're

00:15:38.140 --> 00:15:40.960 align:middle line:90%
really vulnerable with them.

00:15:40.960 --> 00:15:44.800 align:middle line:84%
And the heart is just wide
open and you feel such love.

00:15:44.800 --> 00:15:47.650 align:middle line:84%
And then there's a
comment or a voice inside

00:15:47.650 --> 00:15:51.390 align:middle line:84%
that says, this isn't
safe, it's got to be--

00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:52.990 align:middle line:84%
you've got to do
something different.

00:15:52.990 --> 00:15:54.350 align:middle line:90%
How do you handle that?

00:15:54.350 --> 00:15:56.780 align:middle line:84%
>> I find that from the
space of the open heart,

00:15:56.780 --> 00:15:58.240 align:middle line:90%
I don't get that so much.

00:15:58.240 --> 00:16:02.260 align:middle line:84%
It just feels so good to
be touching heart to heart

00:16:02.260 --> 00:16:06.220 align:middle line:84%
on a real true, intimate
basis with someone,

00:16:06.220 --> 00:16:07.410 align:middle line:90%
just sharing that moment.

00:16:07.410 --> 00:16:09.410 align:middle line:84%
It's so beautiful that
those thoughts don't even

00:16:09.410 --> 00:16:10.257 align:middle line:90%
enter my mind.

00:16:10.257 --> 00:16:11.590 align:middle line:90%
>> You've got the ball with you.

00:16:11.590 --> 00:16:14.410 align:middle line:84%
Because you use that as a
demonstration in your work.

00:16:14.410 --> 00:16:15.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, I do.

00:16:15.400 --> 00:16:16.360 align:middle line:90%
I love using this ball.

00:16:16.360 --> 00:16:18.130 align:middle line:84%
Because it really
demonstrates beliefs,

00:16:18.130 --> 00:16:20.270 align:middle line:84%
as we were talking
about earlier.

00:16:20.270 --> 00:16:23.230 align:middle line:84%
And I use it as an
illustration for self.

00:16:23.230 --> 00:16:28.700 align:middle line:84%
If I think of myself as my name,
my job, my friends and family,

00:16:28.700 --> 00:16:30.610 align:middle line:84%
the people that I
love, everything

00:16:30.610 --> 00:16:32.920 align:middle line:84%
that comprises my
personal universe

00:16:32.920 --> 00:16:34.960 align:middle line:90%
is contained within this ball.

00:16:34.960 --> 00:16:37.330 align:middle line:84%
What happens is, this
contains all the beliefs.

00:16:37.330 --> 00:16:40.190 align:middle line:84%
Because it's what I'm walking
around with day to day.

00:16:40.190 --> 00:16:43.300 align:middle line:84%
And I find that if I can
step outside of my universe

00:16:43.300 --> 00:16:45.490 align:middle line:84%
and began to watch
what I'm thinking,

00:16:45.490 --> 00:16:49.060 align:middle line:84%
watching those thoughts,
the thoughts create beliefs.

00:16:49.060 --> 00:16:51.310 align:middle line:84%
I can choose to
change those thoughts,

00:16:51.310 --> 00:16:53.650 align:middle line:90%
and therefore change my reality.

00:16:53.650 --> 00:17:00.310 align:middle line:84%
>> You have to want to have
a life that is pain-free.

00:17:00.310 --> 00:17:06.460 align:middle line:84%
And the great avatars and
gurus and sages of the ages

00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:12.640 align:middle line:84%
suggest that there is a
burning, that gold is refined

00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:14.438 align:middle line:90%
when there's a burning off.

00:17:14.438 --> 00:17:15.730 align:middle line:90%
I don't know if that's correct.

00:17:15.730 --> 00:17:19.780 align:middle line:84%
But that we do walk
through a fire at times,

00:17:19.780 --> 00:17:22.359 align:middle line:90%
and that fire is painful.

00:17:22.359 --> 00:17:26.089 align:middle line:84%
So do you see a place
for pain in our life?

00:17:26.089 --> 00:17:29.710 align:middle line:84%
>> It served me greatly
in my past experiences.

00:17:29.710 --> 00:17:32.650 align:middle line:84%
I mean, being absolutely
seared to the core.

00:17:32.650 --> 00:17:34.570 align:middle line:84%
Because that levels the
playing field and then

00:17:34.570 --> 00:17:38.150 align:middle line:84%
I was able to go from there to
entirely different experiences.

00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:41.290 align:middle line:84%
But that old truly
needed to be burned away.

00:17:41.290 --> 00:17:44.720 align:middle line:84%
Now it's not to say that I don't
have painful experiences now.

00:17:44.720 --> 00:17:47.120 align:middle line:84%
Because certainly, there's
always more to work on.

00:17:47.120 --> 00:17:50.212 align:middle line:84%
But the valleys aren't as
deep as they were before.

00:17:50.212 --> 00:17:51.920 align:middle line:84%
>> So it's just not
quite as devastating.

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:52.340 align:middle line:90%
>> --more gentle.

00:17:52.340 --> 00:17:52.730 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:17:52.730 --> 00:17:55.190 align:middle line:84%
>> What would be a painful
experience now in a more subtle

00:17:55.190 --> 00:17:57.920 align:middle line:90%
way for you, Catherine?

00:17:57.920 --> 00:18:02.540 align:middle line:84%
>> I think to be away from
love would be very painful.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:04.910 align:middle line:84%
And I speak in a
more universal way,

00:18:04.910 --> 00:18:07.640 align:middle line:84%
to go back to living
very defensively

00:18:07.640 --> 00:18:09.350 align:middle line:90%
and being very closed.

00:18:09.350 --> 00:18:13.490 align:middle line:84%
And that sort of re-emphasizes
that cosmic separation

00:18:13.490 --> 00:18:14.870 align:middle line:90%
that's within all of us.

00:18:14.870 --> 00:18:17.460 align:middle line:84%
But that, to me,
is very painful.

00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:20.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Then how do you feel safe?

00:18:20.310 --> 00:18:23.450 align:middle line:84%
What do you do to support
yourself in experiencing safety

00:18:23.450 --> 00:18:24.380 align:middle line:90%
in the world?

00:18:24.380 --> 00:18:27.200 align:middle line:84%
>> It depends what's going
on on a particular day

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:29.300 align:middle line:84%
at a particular
moment, quite honestly.

00:18:29.300 --> 00:18:31.640 align:middle line:84%
I mean, sometimes I
just want to cocoon

00:18:31.640 --> 00:18:33.560 align:middle line:84%
and I find the safe
place in my home

00:18:33.560 --> 00:18:37.880 align:middle line:84%
and just do whatever I can to be
very kind and loving to myself.

00:18:37.880 --> 00:18:39.000 align:middle line:90%
That creates safety.

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:41.180 align:middle line:90%
Again, it just depends.

00:18:41.180 --> 00:18:45.580 align:middle line:84%
>> When you wrote the
book, what was your intent?

00:18:45.580 --> 00:18:50.180 align:middle line:84%
And is that the same intent now
in sharing it with the world?

00:18:50.180 --> 00:18:54.650 align:middle line:84%
>> The intent is absolutely
to be of service.

00:18:54.650 --> 00:18:59.570 align:middle line:84%
And that intention has
expanded and grown.

00:18:59.570 --> 00:19:02.270 align:middle line:84%
And it's my absolute
delight and joy

00:19:02.270 --> 00:19:05.900 align:middle line:84%
to be out talking with people
and sharing what I've learned.

00:19:05.900 --> 00:19:08.900 align:middle line:84%
>> So your experiences,
you're pretty much,

00:19:08.900 --> 00:19:13.160 align:middle line:84%
you've gone pretty
naked, then, haven't you?

00:19:13.160 --> 00:19:14.760 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, in
writing this book,

00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:18.590 align:middle line:84%
I really debated about whether
I wanted to be that emotionally

00:19:18.590 --> 00:19:20.690 align:middle line:84%
vulnerable,
spiritually vulnerable.

00:19:20.690 --> 00:19:24.560 align:middle line:84%
Did I want to, number one,
be that way toward myself,

00:19:24.560 --> 00:19:27.800 align:middle line:84%
and number two, share that with
those that would read my book?

00:19:27.800 --> 00:19:30.830 align:middle line:84%
But what I found is that if I
can be very honest about what's

00:19:30.830 --> 00:19:33.890 align:middle line:84%
going on in my own
experiences, it

00:19:33.890 --> 00:19:37.070 align:middle line:84%
creates a safe space for others
to become honest about what's

00:19:37.070 --> 00:19:38.480 align:middle line:90%
going on in their lives.

00:19:38.480 --> 00:19:41.870 align:middle line:84%
And through that honesty,
we all find freedom.

00:19:41.870 --> 00:19:45.800 align:middle line:84%
>> I think we are continually
being asked by the universe,

00:19:45.800 --> 00:19:47.690 align:middle line:84%
by God, the God of
our understanding,

00:19:47.690 --> 00:19:51.450 align:middle line:84%
to come back to the moment and
be so present in this moment.

00:19:51.450 --> 00:19:54.320 align:middle line:84%
And it's not something that
we could go to the university

00:19:54.320 --> 00:19:57.540 align:middle line:84%
and come out four years later
and know how to do this.

00:19:57.540 --> 00:20:03.260 align:middle line:84%
You do work with people and
help them understand about time

00:20:03.260 --> 00:20:04.940 align:middle line:90%
and their own rhythms.

00:20:04.940 --> 00:20:08.052 align:middle line:84%
What can you share with
us today about that?

00:20:08.052 --> 00:20:11.130 align:middle line:84%
>> That there are rhythms
in each of our lives.

00:20:11.130 --> 00:20:13.190 align:middle line:84%
There are seasons
in each of our lives

00:20:13.190 --> 00:20:15.170 align:middle line:84%
There is time to
be very proactive

00:20:15.170 --> 00:20:18.560 align:middle line:84%
and create goals and intentions,
and there's other times just

00:20:18.560 --> 00:20:21.440 align:middle line:84%
go with the flow and be
open to listening to what

00:20:21.440 --> 00:20:23.750 align:middle line:90%
the universe has for us.

00:20:23.750 --> 00:20:26.840 align:middle line:84%
>> And what do you
